Document: Joint3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_joint3d.rst  
Summary: Abstract base class for 3D physics joints that bind two physics bodies with constraints.  

Abstract base class for all joints in 3D physics. 3D joints bind together two physics bodies (node_a and node_b) and apply a constraint. If only one body is defined, it is attached to a fixed StaticBody3D without collision shapes. Note: This class serves as a foundation for implementing specific joint types like hinges, sliders, or ball-and-socket joints. It provides shared functionality for connecting rigid bodies while enforcing physical constraints between them. The joint's behavior is determined by its subclass, which defines the specific limitations and forces applied to the connected bodies. Key Rule: Joints require at least one physics body (RigidBody3D or StaticBody3D) to function, with StaticBody3D acting as an implicit anchor when only one body is provided.
---CHUNK---
