Document: Joint3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_joint3d.rst  
Summary: Properties and configuration options for the Joint3D class in Godot, including collision exclusion, node attachment, and solver priority settings.  

exclude_nodes_from_collision (bool): Controls whether the two connected bodies collide with each other. Default: true.  
- set_exclude_nodes_from_collision(value: bool): Sets the collision exclusion state.  
- get_exclude_nodes_from_collision(): Returns the current collision exclusion state.  

node_a (NodePath): Path to the first physics body (A) connected to the joint. Must reference a node inheriting PhysicsBody3D. Default: empty.  
- set_node_a(value: NodePath): Assigns the path for node A.  
- get_node_a(): Retrieves the current path for node A.  
If node_a is empty but node_b is set, the joint connects to a fixed StaticBody3D without collision shapes.  

node_b (NodePath): Path to the second physics body (B) connected to the joint. Must reference a node inheriting PhysicsBody3D. Default: empty.  
- set_node_b(value: NodePath): Assigns the path for node B.  
- get_node_b(): Retrieves the current path for node B.  
If node_b is empty but node_a is set, the joint connects to a fixed StaticBody3D without collision shapes.  

solver_priority (int): Determines the order in which joints are processed by the physics solver. Lower values indicate higher priority. Default: 1.  
- set_solver_priority(value: int): Sets the solver priority.  
- get_solver_priority(): Returns the current solver priority.  
Note: Only functional with GodotPhysics3D. Ignored when using Jolt Physics.
---CHUNK---
